'''Yusuf Abdurisag Yusuf''' ({{langx|so|Yusuf Abdirisaq Yusuf}}, born 6 August 1999) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] side [[Al-Wakrah SC|Al-Wakrah]], on loan from [[Al Sadd SC|Al Sadd]]. Born in Somalia, he plays for the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Club career==
Abdurisag began his professional career with Al Sadd SC in 2018. In January 2019 he was loaned to [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi SC]] and returned in August 2020. In January 2023 he joined [[Al-Wakrah SC]].<ref name="int1">{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/-/551722/ | title=Yusuf Abdurisag | date= | accessdate=2023-03-16}}</ref>

==International career==
In June 2023, during an international friendly against [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]], Abdurisag was accused of racially abusing [[Michael Boxall]]. The match was subsequently abandoned when the New Zealand players refused to return after half-time in protest at referee [[Manuel Schuttengruber]]'s response to the alleged incident.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.startribune.com/new-zealand-qatar-michael-boxall-racially-abused-match-halted-fifa/600283754/|title=Minnesota United's Michael Boxall 'racially abused' in New Zealand vs. Qatar friendly; match halted|newspaper=Star Tribune|date=June 19, 2023|first=Jerry|last=Zgoda}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Nuno Rios |first1=Janina |title=New Zealand abandon friendly against Qatar amid racism allegations |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/new-zealand-abandon-friendly-against-qatar-amid-racism-allegations-2023-06-19/ |access-date=19 June 2023 |work=Reuters |date=19 Jun 2023}}</ref> Abdurisag denied the accusation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Qatar, Kuwait deny racism claims in international football friendlies |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/football/qatar-kuwait-deny-racism-claims-in-international-football-friendlies |access-date=1 July 2023 |work=The Straits Times |date=21 June 2023}}</ref>

